CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 1, 1969, pg. 13, reads: "Conf. Worker 101 - Mrs. Carrie Fuqua, right, who will be 102 years old on Christmas Day, has been a Conference Worker in Allegheny AME Zion Conference for more than a half century, was cited for her labors and consistent attendance at the recent conference session at John Wesley AME Zion Church. Mrs. Mary Meeks, a visiting missionary officer from the Michigan Conference, is seen placing the 'garland of greenbacks' about the shoulders of the very deserving church woman.  Willa Mae Rice, local district president, panned the gesture. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mary Meeks placing garland of dollar bills on Carrie Fuqua during Allegheny AME Zion Conference ceremony, in Wesley Center AME Zion Church
